README.md
     1‚Üí# Tock
     5‚Üí[Features](#features) ‚Ä¢ [Quick Start](#quick-start) ‚Ä¢ [Commands](#commands) ‚Ä¢
     6‚Üí[Configuration](#configuration) ‚Ä¢ [Theme](#theme) ‚Ä¢ [File Format](#file-format) ‚Ä¢ [Shell](#shell-completion) ‚Ä¢ [Inspiration](#inspiration) ‚Ä¢ [License](#license)
     7‚Üí
     8‚Üí## Features
    12‚Üí**Tock** is a powerful time tracking tool for the command line. It saves activity logs as plaintext files and provides an interactive terminal UI for viewing your time.
    13‚Üí
    14‚ÜíFeatures include:
    15‚Üí
    16‚Üí- üìù **Simple plaintext format** - Activities stored in human-readable files
    17‚Üí- üìÖ **Notes & Tags** - Attach detailed notes and tags to activities
    18‚Üí- üé® **Interactive TUI** - Beautiful terminal calendar view using Bubble Tea
    19‚Üí- ‚ö° **Fast & Lightweight** - Single binary, no dependencies
    20‚Üí- üîÑ **Compatible** - Reads/writes Bartib file format and TimeWarrior data files
    21‚Üí- üé® **Customizable Themes** - Multiple color themes and custom color support
    22‚Üí- üìÖ **iCal Export** - Generate .ics files for calendar integration, or sync with system calendars (macOS only)
    23‚Üí
    24‚Üí<hr clear="right"/>
    25‚Üí
    26‚Üí## Quick Start
    28‚Üí### Installation
    30‚Üí#### Homebrew (macOS)
    41‚Üí#### Go Install
    47‚Üí#### Build from source
    53‚Üí#### Install Script (Linux & macOS)
    59‚Üí#### Download Binary
    63‚Üí### Basic Usage
   116‚Üí## Configuration
   118‚ÜíTock supports a flexible configuration system using YAML files and environment variables.
   119‚Üí
   120‚Üí**Priority Order:**
   121‚Üí
   122‚Üí1. Command-line flags
   123‚Üí2. Environment variables
   124‚Üí3. Configuration file (`~/.config/tock/tock.yaml` or `./tock.yaml`)
   125‚Üí4. Default values
   126‚Üí
   127‚Üí### Configuration File
   165‚Üí### Environment Variables
   179‚Üí### Storage Backends
   183‚Üí### 1. Flat File (Default)
   191‚Üí### 2. TimeWarrior
   209‚Üí### Calendar View
   238‚Üí## Theming
   240‚ÜíTock supports customizable color themes for the calendar view.
   241‚Üí
   242‚ÜíYou can configure the theme in `tock.yaml`:
   243‚Üí
   244‚Üí```yaml
   245‚Üítheme:
   246‚Üí  name: custom
   247‚Üí  primary: "#ff0000"
   248‚Üí```
   249‚Üí
   250‚ÜíOr use environment variables:
   251‚Üí
   252‚Üí### Theme Name
   262‚Üí### Auto-detection
   270‚Üí### Custom Colors
   283‚Üí### Example: Cyberpunk / Fuchsia Theme
   300‚Üí### Time Format
   316‚Üí#### 12-Hour Format Examples
   328‚Üí#### 24-Hour Format (Default)
   343‚Üí## Commands
   345‚Üí```bash
   346‚Üí
   347‚ÜíA simple timetracker for the command line
   348‚Üí
   349‚ÜíUsage:
   350‚Üí  tock [command]
   351‚Üí
   352‚ÜíAvailable Commands:
   353‚Üí  add         Add a completed activity
   354‚Üí  analyze     Analyze your productivity patterns
   355‚Üí  calendar    Show interactive calendar view
   356‚Üí  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
   357‚Üí  continue    Continues a previous activity
   358‚Üí  current     Lists all currently running activities
   359‚Üí  help        Help about any command
   360‚Üí  ical        Generate iCal (.ics) file for a specific task, all tasks in a day, or all tasks
   361‚Üí  last        List recent unique activities
   362‚Üí  list        List activities (Calendar View)
   363‚Üí  remove      Remove an activity
   364‚Üí  report      Generate time tracking report
   365‚Üí  start       Start a new activity
   366‚Üí  stop        Stop the current activity
   367‚Üí  version     Print the version info
   368‚Üí  watch       Display a full-screen stopwatch for the current activity
   369‚Üí
   370‚ÜíFlags:
   371‚Üí  -b, --backend string   Storage backend: 'file' (default) or 'timewarrior'
   372‚Üí      --config string    Config file directory (default is $HOME/.config/tock/tock.yaml)
   373‚Üí  -f, --file string      Path to the activity log file (or data directory for timewarrior)
   374‚Üí  -h, --help             help for tock
   375‚Üí  -v, --version          version for tock
   376‚ÜíUse "tock [command] --help" for more information about a command.
   377‚Üí```
   378‚Üí
   379‚Üí[**‚Üí Commands Reference**](docs/commands.md)
   380‚Üí
   381‚Üí### Start tracking
   401‚Üí### Stop tracking
   418‚Üí### Add past activity
   439‚Üí### Remove activity
   453‚Üí### Continue activity
   472‚Üí### Current activity
   482‚Üí### Stopwatch (Watch Mode)
   500‚Üí### Recent activities
   513‚Üí### Calendar View (TUI)
   528‚Üí### Text Report
   551‚Üí### Calendar Integration (iCal)
   578‚Üí### Productivity Analysis
   602‚Üí## Update Check
   604‚ÜíTock automatically checks for updates once a week. When a new version is available, you will see a notification after running commands like `start` or `stop`.
   605‚Üí
   606‚ÜíYou can disable this check by setting `check_updates: false` in your configuration file or using the environment variable `TOCK_CHECK_UPDATES=false`.
   607‚Üí
   608‚Üí## File Format
   610‚ÜíActivities are stored in plaintext format (compatible with Bartib):
   611‚Üí
   612‚Üí```
   613‚Üí  2025-12-10 09:00 - 2025-12-10 11:30 | Project Name | Task description
   614‚Üí  2025-12-10 13:00 | Another Project | Ongoing task
   615‚Üí```
   616‚Üí
   617‚ÜíYou can edit this file manually with any text editor.
   618‚Üí
   619‚Üí## Shell Completion
   621‚ÜíTock supports shell completion for Bash, Zsh, Fish, and PowerShell. This includes basic command completion and **intelligent suggestions** for:
   622‚Üí
   623‚Üí- **Projects**: Suggests existing project names when using `-p` / `--project`.
   624‚Üí- **Descriptions**: Suggests recent activity descriptions when using `-d` / `--description`.
   625‚Üí  - Suggestions are context-aware: if a project is selected, it only suggests descriptions previously used for that project.
   626‚Üí- **Continue IDs**: Suggests valid activity IDs (with details) for the `tock continue` command.
   627‚Üí
   628‚Üí### Installation
   656‚Üí## Shell Integration
   658‚ÜíYou can display the current tracked activity directly in your shell prompt.
   659‚Üí
   660‚Üí### Zsh / Oh My Zsh
   679‚Üí### Starship
   692‚Üí### Technology Stack
   698‚Üí### Project Structure
   709‚Üí## Inspiration
   711‚ÜíTock is inspired by and compatible with [Bartib](https://github.com/nikolassv/bartib) - an excellent time tracking tool written in Rust by Nikolas Schmidt-Voigt. It's saved me countless hours and helped me stay organized, so I wanted to create a similar tool in Go with a clean architecture approach and an interactive terminal UI.
   712‚Üí
   713‚Üí## License
   715‚ÜíGPL-3.0-or-later

